---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const basePath = base.endsWith('/') ? base : `${base}/`;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Build Your Own Tracker — Watchboard"
  description="Create a fully automated, AI-powered intelligence tracker in 25 minutes. Step-by-step guide to launching your own Watchboard topic dashboard."
>
  <main id="main-content">
    <div class="guide-page">
      <a class="guide-back" href={`${basePath}`}>&larr; Watchboard</a>

      <article class="guide-content">
        <div class="guide-header">
          <div class="guide-badge">25 MIN SETUP</div>
          <h1>Build Your Own Tracker</h1>
          <p class="guide-subtitle">
            Any ongoing topic — a conflict, a political crisis, an environmental event, a historical case —
            can become a fully automated Watchboard tracker. The platform handles data updates, maps,
            3D globe, and RSS feeds. You provide the topic.
          </p>
        </div>

        <section>
          <h2>How It Works</h2>
          <p>
            Each tracker is a directory under <code>trackers/{'{slug}'}/</code> containing a
            <code>tracker.json</code> configuration file and a <code>data/</code> folder with JSON
            data files. The site auto-discovers every tracker at build time — no routing code to
            write, no imports to add.
          </p>
          <p>
            The <code>tracker.json</code> defines everything: the topic title, geographic map region,
            dashboard sections, AI search prompts, 3D globe camera presets, and how frequently the
            nightly pipeline should run updates. Once the config exists and the initial seed data is
            populated, the tracker publishes itself.
          </p>
          <div class="info-box">
            <span class="info-label">AUTO-DISCOVERY</span>
            Any directory added to <code>trackers/</code> is automatically picked up by
            <code>getStaticPaths()</code> in the dynamic routes. No manual registration needed.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Step 1: Dispatch the Workflow</h2>
          <p>
            The recommended path is a single GitHub Actions dispatch. Go to the repository's
            <strong>Actions</strong> tab and run <strong>Init New Tracker</strong> with four inputs:
          </p>
          <div class="steps-list">
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>slug</strong>
                <p>
                  A short, URL-safe identifier. Use kebab-case: <code>ukraine-war</code>,
                  <code>amazon-deforestation</code>, <code>taiwan-strait</code>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">2</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>topic</strong>
                <p>
                  A one-sentence description of what this tracker covers. Be specific —
                  the AI uses this to generate the initial config and seed search queries.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">3</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>start_date</strong>
                <p>
                  The earliest date relevant to this tracker, in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> format.
                  The seed job will backfill events from this date forward.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">4</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>region</strong>
                <p>
                  A natural-language description of the geographic area —
                  <code>Middle East</code>, <code>South America</code>, <code>Pacific Rim</code>.
                  Used to configure the 2D map bounds and 3D globe camera starting position.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Step 2: Wait ~25 Minutes</h2>
          <p>
            Two jobs run automatically after the dispatch. You do not need to do anything during this time.
          </p>
          <div class="steps-list">
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">A</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Init Job (~5 min)</strong>
                <p>
                  Claude Code generates <code>tracker.json</code> with full configuration,
                  creates empty data files for all sections, validates the Zod schema,
                  runs a build gate, and commits the scaffolding to <code>main</code>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">B</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Seed Job (~20 min)</strong>
                <p>
                  Claude Code performs deep web research from <code>start_date</code> to today,
                  populating the timeline, map points, KPIs, claims matrix, and all other sections
                  with sourced historical data. Validates and commits on completion.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            The deploy workflow triggers automatically on each commit. By the time the seed job
            finishes, your tracker is already live on GitHub Pages.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Step 3: Your Tracker Is Live</h2>
          <p>
            After the seed commit, your tracker is accessible at
            <code>{'{basePath}'}{'{slug}'}/ </code> with the full dashboard: interactive map,
            3D globe, timeline, and all configured sections. The nightly AI pipeline will
            begin updating it on the configured interval — typically every 1 to 3 days,
            depending on how active the topic is.
          </p>
          <p>
            An RSS feed is generated automatically at <code>{'{slug}'}/rss.xml</code>,
            and an embeddable widget is available at <code>embed/{'{slug}'}/</code> for
            use on external sites.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>What You Get</h2>
          <div class="feature-grid">
            <div class="feature-card">
              <div class="feature-icon">D</div>
              <strong>Dashboard</strong>
              <span>
                Interactive 2D map, KPI strip, sourced timeline, claims matrix,
                political grid, and economic indicators — all auto-updated nightly.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
              <div class="feature-icon">G</div>
              <strong>3D Globe</strong>
              <span>
                CesiumJS globe with animated missile arcs, satellite tracking,
                live flight data, ship AIS, seismic overlays, and cinematic event mode.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
              <div class="feature-icon">AI</div>
              <strong>AI Updates</strong>
              <span>
                Nightly Claude Code agent searches the web, validates sources,
                and updates all data files. Schema-enforced, build-gated, fully auditable.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
              <div class="feature-icon">R</div>
              <strong>RSS Feed</strong>
              <span>
                Per-tracker and global RSS feeds generated at build time.
                Subscribers receive update digests with section summaries after each run.
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Tracker Ideas</h2>
          <p>
            Watchboard works for any structured, ongoing topic with a geographic dimension.
            Some categories that fit well:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Active conflicts</strong> — armed conflicts, border disputes, military operations</li>
            <li><strong>Political crises</strong> — elections, coups, constitutional disputes, sanctions</li>
            <li><strong>Disasters</strong> — nuclear incidents, industrial accidents, hurricanes, earthquakes</li>
            <li><strong>Environmental</strong> — deforestation, pollution events, climate anomalies</li>
            <li><strong>Criminal cases</strong> — organized crime, high-profile investigations, trials</li>
            <li><strong>Historical events</strong> — ongoing investigations into past incidents with new developments</li>
            <li><strong>Economic crises</strong> — currency collapses, sanctions regimes, debt restructurings</li>
            <li><strong>Public health</strong> — outbreaks, epidemic responses, institutional failures</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Manual Setup (Advanced)</h2>
          <p>
            If you prefer full control, you can create a tracker manually in five steps.
            This is the same process the init workflow automates.
          </p>
          <div class="steps-list">
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Copy an existing tracker config</strong>
                <p>
                  Use any <code>trackers/{'{slug}'}/tracker.json</code> as a template.
                  Update the slug, name, shortName, description, mapBounds, and sections array.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">2</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Create the data directory</strong>
                <p>
                  Create <code>trackers/{'{slug}'}/data/</code> with at minimum: <code>meta.json</code>
                  and empty arrays for each section you have enabled in the config.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">3</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Configure AI prompts</strong>
                <p>
                  Set the <code>ai.systemPrompt</code> and <code>ai.searchQueries</code> fields
                  in <code>tracker.json</code>. These drive the nightly update agent's research strategy.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">4</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Verify the build</strong>
                <p>
                  Run <code>npm run build</code>. The tracker auto-discovers and generates pages.
                  Fix any schema validation errors before committing.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">5</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <strong>Seed historical data</strong>
                <p>
                  Dispatch the <strong>Seed Tracker Data</strong> workflow for your new slug,
                  or run the update script locally:
                  <code>TRACKER_SLUG={'{slug}'} npm run update-data</code>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

      </article>

      <div class="guide-cta">
        <p class="cta-text">Have a topic in mind? Open a tracker request on GitHub.</p>
        <a
          class="cta-button"
          href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/watchboard/issues/new?template=tracker-request.yml"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Request a Tracker
        </a>
        <a class="guide-back" href={`${basePath}`}>&larr; Back to Watchboard</a>
      </div>

      <footer class="platform-footer">
        <a href={`${basePath}about/`}>About</a>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <a href={`${basePath}metrics/`}>Status</a>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <a href={`${basePath}social/`}>Social</a>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <a href={`${basePath}guide/`}>Build a Tracker</a>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <a href={`${basePath}rss.xml`}>RSS</a>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <a href="https://x.com/watchboard_dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">X</a>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <a href="https://github.com/ArtemioPadilla/watchboard" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .guide-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  /* ── Back link ── */
  .guide-back {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .guide-back:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-color: var(--border-light);
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  /* ── Page header ── */
  .guide-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .guide-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent-green);
    background: var(--accent-green-dim);
    border: 1px solid rgba(46, 204, 113, 0.25);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .guide-content h1 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .guide-subtitle {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Section headings and body text ── */
  .guide-content h2 {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .guide-content p {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .guide-content code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--accent-amber);
  }

  /* ── Info box ── */
  .info-box {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-blue);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .info-box code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    background: rgba(52, 152, 219, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(52, 152, 219, 0.2);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--accent-blue);
  }
  .info-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  /* ── Numbered steps ── */
  .steps-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .step-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
  }

  .step-num {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
    background: var(--accent-blue);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: 0.05rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .step-body strong {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .step-body p {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .step-body code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--accent-amber);
  }

  /* ── Feature grid ── */
  .feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .feature-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .feature-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-light);
  }

  .feature-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    background: var(--accent-blue-dim);
    border: 1px solid rgba(52, 152, 219, 0.2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .feature-card strong {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .feature-card span {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ── Ideas list ── */
  .guide-content ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .guide-content ul li {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .guide-content ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.72rem;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--accent-green);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .guide-content ul li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* ── CTA footer ── */
  .guide-cta {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-text {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cta-button {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-blue);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.2rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.1s;
  }
  .cta-button:hover {
    background: #2980b9;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .cta-button:active {
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  /* ── Platform footer ── */
  .platform-footer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .platform-footer a {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .platform-footer a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-blue);
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .guide-page { padding: 1.5rem 1rem 3rem; }
    .guide-content h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    .feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .step-item { padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 400px) {
    .feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
